iation#Awards|Korean Goal of the Year]]: [[2010 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 AFC Fourth Round#Group B|2008]], [[Football at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament#Bronze medal match|2012]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sports.news.naver.com/general/news/read.nhn?oid=020&aid=0002015751 |script-title=ko:\uc62c \ucd5c\uace0\uc758 \uace8\uc740 \ubc15\uc8fc\uc601 \uc0ac\uc6b0\ub514\uc804 \uc410\uae30\uace8 |website=Naver.com |publisher=Dong-A Ilbo |language=ko |date=31 December 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kfa.or.kr/news/news_view.asp?BoardNo=9437&Page=1&Query=PageSize%3D10%26Gubun%3D11311%26Key%3D3%26Word%3D%EB%B2%A0%EC%8A%A4%ED%8A%B8 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305013120/http://www.kfa.or.kr/news/news_view.asp?BoardNo=9437&Page=1&Query=PageSize%3D10%26Gubun%3D11311%26Key%3D3%26Word%3D%EB%B2%A0%EC%8A%A4%ED%8A%B8 |script-title=ko:\ud32c\ub4e4\uc774 \uc120\uc815\ud55c \u2018\uc62c\ud574\uc758 \ubca0\uc2a4\ud2b8\u2019 \ucd5c\uace0 \uacbd\uae30\ub294 \uc77c\ubcf8\uc804! |publisher=KFA |language=ko |date=27 December 2012 |archive-date=5 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nPark is a [[Christianity|Christian]]. Park writes [[Jesus|Jesus Christ]] next to his autograph and has spoken about his faith saying, \"The first and main reason why I play football is to evangelise people.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Arsenal steal South Korean idol Park Chu Young from Lille|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/arsenal/8727273/Arsenal-steal-South-Korean-idol-Park-Chu-Young-from-Lille.html}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Park Chu-Young}}\n* [http://www.kfa.or.kr/archive/player_history.php?search_val=%EB%B0%95%EC%A3%BC%EC%98%81 Park Chu-young \u2013 National Team Stats] at [[Korea Football Association|KFA]] {{in lang|ko}}\n* {{K League player|20050094}}\n* {{FIFA player|207761|Park Chuyoung}}\n* {{LFP|park-chu-young|Chu Young Park}}\n* {{ESPN FC|65421<!-- /park-chu-young -->|Park Chu-Young}}\n* {{Soccerbase|name=Park Chu-Young}}\n* {{NFT player|8123|Chu-Young Park}}\n\n{{FC Seoul squad}}\n{{Navboxes\n| titlestyle=background:gold; color:black;\n| title=Awards\n| list1=\n{{2005 K-League Best XI}}\n{{K League Young Player}}\n{{Asian Young Footballer of the Year}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes\n|titlestyle=background:#F02A18; color:white;\n|title= South Korea squads\n|list1=\n{{South Korea squad 2006 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{South Korea men's football squad 2008 Summer Olympics}}\n{{South Korea squad 2010 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{South Korea men's football squad 2012 Summer Olympics}}\n{{South Korea squad 2014 FIFA World Cup}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Park, Chu-young}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Daegu]]\n[[Category:South Korean footballers]]\n[[Category:South Korean expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:South Korea under-20 international footballers]]\n[[Category:South Korea under-23 international footballers]]\n[[Category:South Korea international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:FC Seoul players]]\n[[Category:AS Monaco FC players]]\n[[Category:Arsenal F.C. players]]\n[[Category:RC Celta de Vigo players]]\n[[Category:Al-Shabab FC (Riyadh) players]]\n[[Category:2014 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:K League 1 players]]\n[[Category:Ligue 1 players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:La Liga players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Monaco]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Spain]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Saudi Arabia]]\n[[Category:2006 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 2008 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:2010 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic footballers of South Korea]]\n[[Category:South Korean expatriate sportspeople in Monaco]]\n[[Category:South Korean expatriate sportspeople in England]]\n[[Category:South Korean expatriate sportspeople in Spain]]\n[[Category:South Korean expatriate sportspeople in Saudi Arabia]]\n[[Category:Korea University alumni]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in football]]\n[[Category:Olympic bronze medalists for South Korea]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Asian Young Footballer of the Year winners]]\n[[Category:Asian Games medalists in football]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 2006 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 2010 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Asian Games bronze medalists for South Korea]]\n[[Category:Saudi Professional League players]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2010 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:South Korean Christians]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|a footballer|the long-distance runner|Park Ju-young}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2012}}\n{{Korean name|Park}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name               = Park Chu-young\n| image              = FC\uc11c\uc6b8 2016 K\ub9ac\uadf8 \uc6b0\uc2b9! \ud669\uc120\ud64d\uac10\ub3c5 \ubc15\uc8fc\uc601, \ub2e4\uce74\ud558\uae30 \uc778\ud130\ubdf0 0.51 minutes Scene.jpg\n| image_size         = \n| caption            = Park Chu-young in November 2016\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1985|7|10|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[Daegu]], South Korea\n| height             = 1.82 m<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.premierleague.com/en-gb/players/profile.html/chu-young-park|title=Player Profile: Chu-Young Park|publisher=Premier League|accessdate=31 January 2012}}</ref>\n| position           = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub        = [[FC Seoul]]\n| clubnumber         = 10\n| youthyears1        = 2001\u20132003 |youthclubs1 = [[Cheonggu High School]]\n| youthyears2        = 2002      |youthclubs2 = \u2192 [[Zico Football Center]] (loan)\n| youthyears3        = 2004      |youthclubs3 = [[Korea University]]\n| years1             = 2005\u20132008 |clubs1 = [[FC Seoul