r Management''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2019/04/25/rico-nastys-anger-management-is-here|title=Rico Nasty's Anger Management is here|website=The FADER|language=en|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref>'''\n* 01. \"Cold\"\n* 02. \"Cheat Code\" (featuring [[Baauer]])\n* 03. \"Hatin\"\n* 04. \"Big Titties\" (featuring Baauer & [[EarthGang|EARTHGANG]])\n* 05. \"Nasty World (skit)\"\n* 06. \"Relative\"\n* 07. \"Mood\" (featuring Splurge)\n* 08. \"Sell Out\"\n* 09. \"Again\"\n\n;Zack Fox and Kenny Beats -\n* \"Jesus Is the One (I Got Depression)\"<ref>{{Citation|title=Zack Fox & Kenny Beats \u2013 Jesus Is the One (I Got Depression)|url=https://genius.com/Zack-fox-and-kenny-beats-jesus-is-the-one-i-got-depression-lyrics|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\n;[[Dominic Fike]] - ''Untitled Debut Album''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/pigeons-and-planes/2019/01/dominic-fike-interview|title=Now or Never: The Chaotic Rise of Dominic Fike|website=Complex|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\n* \"Phone Numbers\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2019/07/04/dominic-fike-kenny-beats-phone-numbers-2019-stream|title=Dominic Fike and Kenny Beats link up on \"Phone Numbers\"|website=The FADER|language=en|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref>\n\n;[[Ed Sheeran]] - ''[[No.6 Collaborations Project]]''\n* 04. \"Take Me Back to London\" (featuring [[Stormzy]]) {{small|(produced with [[Skrillex]] and [[Fred Again|FRED]])}}<ref>{{Citation|title=Ed Sheeran (Ft. Stormzy) \u2013 Take Me Back to London|url=https://genius.com/Ed-sheeran-take-me-back-to-london-lyrics|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\n;[[Gucci Mane]] - ''[[Delusions of Grandeur (Gucci Mane album)|Delusions of Grandeur]]\n* 06. \"Proud of You\" {{small|(produced with Nils)}}<ref>{{Citation|title=Gucci Mane \u2013 Proud of You|url=https://genius.com/Gucci-mane-proud-of-you-lyrics|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n* 15. \"Us\"<ref>{{Citation|title=Gucci Mane \u2013 Us|url=https://genius.com/Gucci-mane-us-lyrics|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\n;Rexx Life Raj - ''Father Figure 3: Somewhere Out There''\n\n* 03. \"Moonwalk\"<ref>{{Citation|title=Rexx Life Raj & Kenny Beats \u2013 Moonwalk|url=https://genius.com/Rexx-life-raj-and-kenny-beats-moonwalk-lyrics|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\n;[[Yung Bans]] - [[Misunderstood (album)|''Misunderstood'']]\n\n* 07. \"Touch the Stars (featuring Lil TJay)\"<ref>{{Citation|title=Yung Bans (Ft. Lil Tjay) \u2013 Touch The Stars|url=https://genius.com/Yung-bans-touch-the-stars-lyrics|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\n;[[FKA twigs]] - ''[[Magdalene (album)|Magdalene]]''\n* 04. \"Holy Terrain (feat. [[Future (rapper)|Future]])\" {{small|(produced with FKA twigs, [[Jack Antonoff]], [[Skrillex]], [[Sounwave]], Lewis Roberts, and Noah Goldstein)}}<ref>{{Citation|title=FKA twigs (Ft. Future) \u2013 holy terrain|url=https://genius.com/Fka-twigs-holy-terrain-lyrics|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\n;[[DaBaby]] - ''[[Kirk (album)|Kirk]]''\n* 08. \"Toes (featuring [[Lil Baby]] & [[Moneybagg Yo]])\" {{small|(produced with Queen Sixties)}}<ref>{{Citation|title=DaBaby (Ft. Lil Baby & Moneybagg Yo) \u2013 TOES|url=https://genius.com/Dababy-toes-lyrics|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\n;[[03 Greedo]] and Kenny Beats - ''Netflix and Deal''\n* 01. \"Traffic\" {{small|(produced with Captain Crunch)}}\n* 02. \"Paid in Full\" {{small|(produced with Nils)}}\n* 03. \"Disco Shit\" (featuring [[Freddie Gibbs]])\n* 04. \"Maria\" {{small|(produced with 1Mind)}}\n* 05. \"Blue People\" (featuring [[Vince Staples]])\n* 06. \"Beg Your Pardon\" (featuring [[Maxo Kream]])\n* 07. \"Honey I Shrunk The Kids\" \n* 08. \"Brad Pitt\" {{small|(produced with Nils)}}\n* 09. \"Aye Twin\" (featuring Key!) {{small|(produced with [[100 gecs|Dylan Brady]])}}\n* 10. \"Life\" \n* 11. \"Payback\" (featuring [[Shoreline Mafia|Ohgeesy]]) {{small|(produced with Judge Beats)}}\n* 12. \"Soul Food\" (featuring [[Buddy (rapper)|Buddy]]) {{small|(produced with [[Phony Ppl|Elijah Rawk]])}}\n* 13. \"Dead Presidents\"\n\n=== 2020 ===\n;[[IDLES]] - ''TBC''\n\n'''[[Key Glock]]''' '''- ''Yellow Tape'''''\n\n* 11. Loaded\n\n[[Denzel Curry|'''Denzel Curry''']] '''and Kenny Beats''' '''''- [[Unlocked_(EP)|UNLOCKED]]'''''\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:American hip hop record producers]]\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| background       = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| genre            = [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[Loudpvck]]|[[Vince Staples]]|[[Rico Nasty]]|KEY!|[[Freddie Gibbs]]|[[JPEGMafia]]|[[Denzel Curry]]|[[FKA twigs]]}}\n| birth_name       = Kenneth Charles Blume III\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1991|5|10|mf=yes}}\n| birth_place      = [[Greenwich, Connecticut]], U.S.\n| module           = {{Infobox person\n| embed            = yes\n| height           = 6 feet 7 inches{{cn|date=March 2020}} \n}}\n| instrument       = {{hlist|[[Digital audio workstation]]|[[Ableton Live]]|[[drums]]|[[guitar]]}}\n| caption          = Kenny Beats at Hard Summer 2019 music festival\n| image            = [[File:Kenny Beats at Hard Summer 2019.png|frameless|Kenny Beats at Hard Summer 2019]]\n}}\n\n'''Kenneth Charles Blume III''' (born May 10, 1991), known professionally as '''Kenny Beats''', is an American record producer and songwriter. He has produced songs with Tisakorean, [[Zack Fox]], [[Vince Staples]], [[Freddie Gibbs]], KEY!, [[Gucci Mane]], [[Ski Mask the Slump God]], [[Dominic Fike]], [[Rico Nasty]] and [[JPEGMafia]], among many others.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/kenny-beats-rap-03-greedo-vince-staples-rico-nasty-770433/|title=Kenny Beats Is a Rap Therapist Who Will Also Make You a Great Album|last=Holmes|first=Charles|last2=Holmes|first2=Charles|date=2019-01-20|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nBlume was born in Greenwich, Connecticut, and grew up there. He started playing guitar at the age of 9 and began drumming at the age of 11.  After he came 2nd in a national electronic music competition,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kennybeats.wordpress.com/biography/|title=Biography|date=2008-12-28|website=www.kennybeats.com|language=en|access-date=2019-12-13}}</ref> he began to take music seriously. After he graduated high school he moved to New York, where he interned for Cinematic Music Group's Jonny Shipes.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Schube |first1=Will |title=\u201cKenny Beats Is Hip-Hop Production's Prodigal Son.\u201d |url=https://pitchfork.com/levels/kenny-beats-is-hip-hop-productions-prodigal-son/ |website=Pitchfork}}</ref> After spending some time in NY, he moved to Boston and studied Jazz Guitar and Music Business at Berklee College of Music.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Schwartz |first1=Danny |title=How Kenny Beats Became the Hottest Rap Producer on the Planet |url=https://www.theringer.com/music/2018/12/14/18139824/kenny-beats-best-rap-producer-2018-key-vince-staples-freddie-gibbs |website=The Ringer}}</ref>.\n\n== Musical style ==\nKenny is known to tailor his production to artists' requests, helping them develop their own individual sound. He handles vocal production as well as instrumental and frequently mixes and masters the final products. His YouTube series \"The Cave\" highlights his frequent use of [[Ableton Live]].\n\nHis songs often begin with the tagline \"Woah, Kenny!\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/levels/kenny-beats-is-hip-hop-productions-prodigal-son/|title=Kenny Beats Is Hip-Hop Production's Prodigal Son|website=Pitchfork|language=en|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref>\n\n== LOUDPVCK ==\nIn 2009, while attending Berklee College of Music, Kenny met Ryan Marks, a DJ. These two became friends, and in 2012, they decided to form the EDM duo [[Loudpvck]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Watson |first1=Elijah |title=Kenny Beats Wants To Be Rap's Quincy Jones [Interview] |url=https://www.okayplayer.com/originals/who-is-kenny-beats-rico-nasty-777.html |website=OkayPlayer}}</ref>. The group had a successful run, releasing plenty of successful original music, but solidified themselves as a force once they collaborated with bigger artists, such as NGHTMRE and Zeds Dead. In 2017, the two parted ways and went on to pursue solo endeavors.\n\n== Social media presence ==\n\nBeginning in March 2019, Kenny launched a YouTube series called \"The Cave\", in which he invites artists to rap 16-32 bars over a custom beat he creates during the video.  Usually, the artists are people that he already has experience with, or, is already friends with<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dazeddigital.com/music/article/46394/1/kenny-beats-how-to-produce-a-legendary-rap-freestyle-interview|title=Kenny Beats\u2019 guide to producing a legendary rap freestyle|last=Dazed|date=2019-10-21|website=Dazed|language=en|access-date=2019-12-13}}</ref>.  They come in, tell him what kind of beat they want, and in 10 to 15 minutes, he'll have something ready that caters to that particular style. The Cave is known for showcasing not only these artists' lyricism, but their personalities. As of April 1, 2020, he has uploaded 23 episodes and amassed just over 31 million views. Guests of The Cave include [[Vince Staples]], [[JPEGMafia]], [[Freddie Gibbs]], [[Rico Nasty]], [[EARTHGANG]], [[Lil Yachty]], [[Smino]], [[Denzel Curry]], [[Zack Fox]], [[Doja Cat]], [[Thundercat (musician)|Thundercat]], [[Danny Brown]], [[6lack]], [[Slowthai]], Sada Baby, [[Marc Rebillet]] and [[Joji_(musician)|Joji]].\n\nIn March 2020, as a result of the [[Coronavirus_disease_2019|Coronavirus epidemic]], Kenny started a [[Twitch_(service)|Twitch]] stream where he makes beats, breaks down famous songs he's produced, talks with other artists and producers, and gives out advice relating to music and the music industry. His stream garners thousands of viewers every day.\n\n== Production discography ==\n\n=== 2010 ===\n;[[Smoke DZA]] - ''Substance Abuse 1.5: The Headstash''\n*02. \"Headstash\" (featuring Den10)\n\n; Smoke DZA - ''George Kush Da Button''\n* 01. \"Continental Kush Breakfast\" (featuring Den10)\n\n=== 2011 ===\n\n;Smoke DZA - ''The Hustler's Catalog''\n* 14. \"Profit\" {{small|(produced with 183rd)}}\n\n;Smoke DZA - ''Rolling Stoned''\n* 05. \"Ball Game\" (featuring [[Kendrick Lamar]]) {{small|(produced with 183rd)}}\n* 09. \"Pow Wow\" (featuring [[Dom Kennedy]]) {{small|(produced with 183rd)}}\n\n;[[Skeme]] - ''Before My Next Statement''\n* 05. \"Truth\"\n\n; Smoke DZA - ''Sweet Baby Kushed God''\n* 01. \"Smokey Klause\" {{small|(produced with 183rd)}}\n\n=== 2012 ===\n;[[Schoolboy Q|ScHoolboy Q]] -\n* \"Party\"\n\n;[[Smoke DZA]] - ''K.O.N.Y.''\n* 09. \"Diamond\" (featuring [[Ab-Soul]])\n\n;Skeme - ''Alive & Living''\n* 16. \"Everything On Me\"\n\n;[[Jet Life]] - ''[[Jet World Order 2]]''\n* 06. \"24 Hrs\" (featuring [[Trademark Da Skydiver]] and [[Young Roddy]])\n\n=== 2014 ===\n;[[Ab-Soul]] - ''[[These Days... (album)|These Days...]]''\n* 03. \"Hunnid Stax\" (featuring ScHoolboy Q)\n\n=== 2016 ===\n;[[Lucki]] - ''[[Son of Sam (EP)|Son of Sam]]''\n* 01. \"Double Check\"\n* 02. \"His Only...\"\n\n;Skywlkr - ''Joints''\n* 01. \"3 Drugs\" (featuring Kenny Beats) {{small|[produced with Skywlkr]}}\n\n=== 2017 ===\n;Lucki -\n* \"Live It\"\n\n;[[Hoodrich Pablo Juan]] and Kenny Beats - ''South Dark''<ref>https://music.apple.com/gb/album/south-dark-ep/1268318300</ref>\n* 01. \"Dead End\"\n* 02. \"Everyday\"\n* 03. \"Ruthless\" (featuring Duke)\n* 04. \"Do This\"\n* 05. \"C Sick\"\n* 06. \"3 Point Stance\"\n* 07. \"Hood\" (featuring Baby Uiie)\n\n;DJ Lucas -\n* \"Big Dope\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://graduationmusic.org/2017/08/26/dj-lucas-big-dope-prod-kenny-beats/|title=DJ Lucas \u2013 \"Big Dope\" [Prod. Kenny Beats]|last=Fay|first=Seamus|date=2017-08-26|website=graduationmusic.org|language=en|access-date=2019-08-07}}</ref>\n\n;Lil Wop - ''Wopavelli 3''\n* 05. \"Topgolf\"\n* 09. \"Dope Man\"\n* 10. \"Walking Dead\"\n* 11. \"Friday the 13th\"\n* 14. \"Grow Up\"\n* 16. \"Xans\" {{small|(produced with ChaseTheMoney)}}\n\n=== 2018 ===\n;[[YoungBoy Never Broke Again]] - ''[[Until Death Call My Name]]''\n* 09. \"Traumatized\" {{small|(produced with Judge)}}\n\n;[[Two-9|Key!]] and Kenny Beats - ''777''\n* 01. \"Demolition 1 + 2\"\n* 02. \"Hater\"\n* 03. \"Blurry\"\n* 04. \"Boss\"\n* 05. \"Move\"\n* 06. \"Famous\"\n* 07. \"It Gets Better\"\n* 08. \"Kelly Price Freestyle\"\n* 09. \"Love On Ice\"\n* 10. \"Dig It\"\n* 11. \"Toronto\"\n* 12. \"True Love Interlude\"\n* 13. \"Control\"\n* 14. \"Twisted\"\n* 15. \"Squeamish\"\n\n;[[Freddie Gibbs]] - ''[[Freddie (Freddie Gibbs album)|Freddie]]''\n* 02. \"Automatic\"\n* 03. \"Death Row\" {{small|(featuring [[03 Greedo]]; produced with Freddie Kane)}}\n* 07. \"Set Set\"\n* 08. \"Toe Tag\"\n* 09. \"FBC\" {{small|(produced with A. Lau and Tony Seltzer)}}\n\n;[[Zack Fox]] - \n* \"Square Up\"\n\n;[[Vince Staples]] - ''[[FM!]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/fm!-mw0003223816|title=FM! - Vince Staples {{!}} Songs, Reviews, Credits|website=AllMusic|language=en-us|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref>'''\n* 01. \"Feels Like Summer\"\n* 02. \"Outside!\"\n* 03. \"Don't Get Chipped\" {{small|(produced with [[Cubeatz]])}}\n* 05. \"New earlsweatshirt\"\n* 07. \"FUN!\" {{small|(produced with Hagler)}}\n* 08. \"No Bleedin\"\n* 09. \"Brand New Tyga\"\n* 10. \"(562) 453-9382\"\n* 11. \"Tweakin\" {{small|(produced with KillaGraham)}}\n\n;[[JPEGMafia]] and Kenny Beats -\n* \"Puff Daddy\"\n\n;10k.Caash - ''The Creator''\n* 02. \u201cMutumbo\u201d {{small|(featuring [[Rico Nasty]])}}\n* 10. \"Aloha\" {{small|(featuring GUN40)}}\n\n;[[JID]] - ''[[DiCaprio 2]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/dicaprio-2-mw0003230938|title=DiCaprio 2 - JID {{!}} Songs, Reviews, Credits|website=AllMusic|language=en-us|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref>\n* 